{
  "answer": "In 'Ishq par zor nahin' (the closing couplet/maqta of Diwan-E-Ghalib, chapter 157, titled 'Nukta-cheen hai gham-e-dil uss ko sunaye na bane'), Ghalib says: 'On love, O Ghalib, you can have no force or sway; it is a fire you can't light, or allay—it cannot be.' The Urdu transliteration reads: 'Ishq par zor nahin hai yeh woh aatish Ghalib / Ke lagaye na lage aur bujhaye na bane.' The verse conveys that love is beyond human will or control — it is a flame that cannot be kindled by choice nor extinguished by effort.",
